@RKphotographic The equation for straight line is y=mx+c
C is where it cuts the y axis, here it’s  -6
M is the slope. Can be worked out by dividing change in y by change in x
So here for every 3 units of y, x changes by 1, so slope is 3
Slope is positive since it’s rising
Answer is y = 3x - 6
